The cerebral vascular response to a rapid decrease in blood glucose to values above normal in poorly controlled type 1 (insulin-dependent) diabetes mellitus. The effect of rapid lowering of blood glucose on cerebral blood flow (CBF) was studied in 10 Type 1 (insulin-dependent) diabetic patients (age 23.5 +/- 3.8 years mean +/- S.D.) with longstanding, poor metabolic control (HbAlc 11.2 +/- 1.0%